Greetings from Los Angeles and welcome back to In the Room. If you
listen to one diss track today, make it Sam Altman=E2=80=99s rejection of E=
lon Musk=E2=80=99s $97.4 billion offer for OpenAI. =E2=80=9CI think he=E2=
=80=99s probably just trying to slow us down,=E2=80=9D Altman told ( https:=
//www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-02-11/altman-blasts-musk-s-purchase-=
offer-as-attempt-to-slow-openai?utm_campaign=3DIn+the+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%2=
82%2F12%2F25%29&utm_content=3DIn+The+Room+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F12%2F25%29&u=
tm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42ab=
d12a ) Bloomberg TV. =E2=80=9CI wish he would just compete by building a be=
tter product, but I think there=E2=80=99s been a lot of
tactics=E2=80=94many, many lawsuits, all sorts of other crazy stuff. Now th=
is.=E2=80=9D When asked if he thought Musk=E2=80=99s offer was driven by in=
